<h4><a target="_blank" href="https://www.ub.uni-leipzig.de/forschungsbibliothek/historische-bestaende/archive/#c1070">Dance Archive Leipzig</a></h4>

<p>
Founded in 1957 as a collection of traditional folkloric items, the Leipzig Dance Archive has since expanded
to become a documentation centre representing all types of dance. By the time of his death in 1984, Petermann
had established the Archive as a well-recognized institution contributing to an understanding of dance as a
cultural phenomenon. In 1975, the Archive became an associate member of the German Democratic Republic’s Academy
of Arts. Since 1993, the Dance Archive has been run as a non-profit association founded by the University of
Leipzig and the Felix Mendelssohn Bartholdy Academy of Music and Theatre. In 2011, the Leipzig Dance Archive
was taken on the University of Leipzig Library. The documents and other items are divided into a specialised
library and the dance archive collection, which includes film recordings from the second half of the 20th century,
literary collections, full and partial inherited private collections, posters, photographs, postcards, microfilm
and other archive material. Some of the documents and other items have been entered into a database which can be
viewed in the special collections and using University of Leipzig Library computers. </p>

